City to tend to their skin, and to grapple with the damage caused by the war's lingering toxicity. In showing how the US military laid the foundations for contemporary Vietnamese consumption of cosmetics and practices of beauty, Tu shows how the intersecting histories of militarism, biomedicine, race, and aesthetics become materially and metaphorically visible on skin.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aChemical warfarexHealth aspectszVietnam. 0aMedicine, PreventivezVietnam. 0aSkinxDiseaseszVietnam. 0aVietnam War, 1961-1975xChemical warfarexHealth aspects. 0aVietnam War, 1961-1975xMedical care. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Ethnic Studies / Asian American Studies.2bisacsh  aAlbert Klingman.  amilitary dermatology.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311074331908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021 Englishz978311075418608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021z9783110753967oZDB-23-DSL40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978147801313640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478013136423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478013136/original  a978-3-11-074331-9  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075418-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021 Englishb2021  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2021  aZDB-23-DSLb2021